{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Purugly}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Normal|prevnum=431|prev=Glameow|nextnum=433|next=Chingling|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Purugly}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Purugly\n|jname=ブニャット\n|tmname=Bunyatto\n|ndex=432\n|sdex=077\n|abrow=040\n|obrow=163\n|opbrow=148\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Normal\n|category=Tiger Cat\n|height-ftin=3\'03"\n|height-m=1.0\n|weight-lbs=96.6\n|weight-kg=43.8\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Thick Fat\n|ability2=Own Tempo\n|abilityd=Defiant\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evsp=2\n|expyield=158\n|oldexp=183\n|lv100exp=800,000\n|gendercode=191\n|color=Gray\n|catchrate=75\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=purugly\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Purugly\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ブニャット\'\'\' \'\'Bunyatto\'\') is a {{type|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s from {{p|Glameow}} starting at [[level]] 38.\n\n==Biology==\nPurugly is a rotund gray and white feline Pokémon with a crescent-shaped head. Its ears are pointed and tipped purple. It has whiskers with a zigzag-like pattern at the end of them. The frilly portion of its spiraling tail is forked, but it usually keeps it clasped around its waist. Despite appearing very sluggish, Purugly will not be reluctant to attack if angered and can be quite fast.\n\nPurugly attempts to make itself look larger and more intimidating by cinching its waist with its forked tail. It barges into the nests of other Pokémon and frighten them off so Purugly can claim the nest as its own. It can be found in both urban areas and heavily wooded forests.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Mamie Purugly.png|thumb|230px|left|Purugly in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Mars\'s Purugly]]====\n[[Mars]]\'s Purugly appeared in \'\'[[DP097|Double Team Turnover!]]\'\', which also marked the species\' main series debut. It reappeared in \'\'[[DP110|Steeling Peace of Mind!]]\'\' and \'\'[[DP111|Saving the World From Ruins!]]\'\'.\n\n====Other====\n[[Mamie]]\'s Glameow evolved into a Purugly in \'\'[[DP178|For The Love Of Meowth!]]\'\', after it was hurt by [[James\'s Carnivine]]\'s {{m|Bullet Seed}}. {{MTR}} had been attracted to Purugly as a Glameow, but once it evolved and had a sudden personality change, Meowth lost all interest.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nPurugly debuted in a cameo in \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\', where it was seen on a rooftop.\n\nA Purugly made a small cameo in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nA Purugly appeared in \'\'[[DP161|Yes in Dee Dee, It\'s Dawn!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Coordinator}}. It was used along with a {{p|Roserade}} for the [[Double Performance]] required during the {{to|Daybreak}} {{pkmn|Contest}}.\n\nA Purugly made a brief appearance in \'\'[[DP182|An Old Family Blend!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Trainer}} participating in the [[Lily of the Valley Conference]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP178|Purugly|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Purugly, the Tiger Cat Pokémon, and the evolved form of Glameow. By rounding its tail around itself, it can appear to be bigger, and when locking eyes with another, it can stare forever.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Mars Purugly Adventures.png|thumb|250px|Purugly in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n[[File:Mars Purugly PMDP.png|thumb|200px|Purugly in {{OBP|Pocket Monsters DP|Kosaku Anakubo}}]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Mars\'s Purugly}}\nPurugly appears in \'\'[[PS344|Belligerent Bronzor]]\'\' under the ownership of [[Mars]]. While bulky, Purugly is a powerful battler that aided her escape from the [[Valley Windworks]]. Mars later calls upon Purugly to battle {{adv|Diamond}}, defeating the {{TP|Fantina|Drifblim}} [[Fantina]] entrusted to him.\n\nA Purugly appeared in a picture in \'\'[[PAORAS04|Omega Alpha Adventure 4]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\n{{main|Mars\'s Purugly}}\nPurugly also appears as one of [[Mars]]\'s Pokémon in [[Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure!]], and was sent out to fight [[Hareta]] and {{OBP|Jun|DPA}} in \'\'[[DPA03|The Mystery Boy, Jun!!]]\'\'. Purugly had the upper hand when it cut the power to the Valley Windworks, but Hareta\'s {{p|Shinx}} solved the problem by restoring power with its {{m|Spark}}. It later battled, and was quickly defeated by, {{p|Deoxys}}.\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\n{{main|Mars\'s Purugly}}\nMars\'s Purugly appeared in [[PMDP13]].\n{{-}}\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Purugly (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n{{spoilers}}\n* {{g|Mystery Dungeon: Gates to Infinity}}: Purugly appears as one of the chief commanders of [[Munna (Gates to Infinity)|Munna]]\'s gang that was enlisted by [[Kyurem (Gates to Infinity)|Kyurem]] to help eliminate any humans that came to the Pokémon world to stop the [[Bittercold]]. At the [[Glacier Palace]], she gets together a group of {{p|Excadrill}} as part of helping to ward off the player, partner, and their teammates.\n{{endspoilers}}\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Normal}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=077|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon\'s nest and claims it as its own.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=It binds its body with its tails to make itself look bigger. If it locks eyes, it will glare ceaselessly.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=It would claim another Pokémon\'s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|re